description.narrative: “Nsa Kenno” (Yes, We Can do it) adopted by the GCO as part of 2019 AMP system of programming is to reinforce the principles of human right based programing, focuses on delivering community-based activities through the existing local governance mechanisms, with the inclusion and participation of children, adolescents and youth. It places people at the center as agent of change, linking communities with duty bearers. The aim is to strengthen capacities of local governance structures and community-based Organizations that supported implementation of high-quality standard and evidence-based community engagement to drive a social transformation in behaviour and demand for services. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:27/12/2019
